snippet.textDisplay: This song is an ancient folk song(Palligeeti)from british Tripura District which is now known as Comilla Zilla in Bangladesh! And this song was widly sung by Dotora Musician in mostly north west bengal of Greater India for hundreds of year.Baut this song was first came in lime light when a Royal member Pratima Pandey of Gouripur of Dhubri District!  sung this song!
snippet.textOriginal: This song is an ancient folk song(Palligeeti)from british Tripura District which is now known as Comilla Zilla in Bangladesh! And this song was widly sung by Dotora Musician in mostly north west bengal of Greater India for hundreds of year.Baut this song was first came in lime light when a Royal member Pratima Pandey of Gouripur of Dhubri District!  sung this song!

snippet.textDisplay: To all the confused people, this song started in Assam, then spread to Bengal(back then Bengal contained West Bengal, Bangladesh, Bihar and some parts of North East). So there are a few different variations of it. The original one is in golpariya(sorry for the spelling) , and there are many other variations in different Bengali dialects. Since Assamese and Bengali is quite similar it's a little hard to differentiate between the two versions. The song used here is the Bengali one spoken in the standard Bengali dialect. All the butthurt Bangladeshis stop acting as if this song belongs only to you guys.
